title: Life Is Good Tour
description:
Multi-platinum hip hop legend Nas hits the capital on Tuesday 19th March 2013, taking over The O2 Arena in support of his 10th album "Life Is Good". Current single "Cherry Wine" is out now and features the late Amy Winehouse. It was his friendship with Amy that led Nas' to donate Â£1 from every ticket sold to the Amy Winehouse Foundation, set up in Amy's memory to support charitable activities in the UK and abroad.

Support comes from hip hop's youngest rising star Meek Mill. He'll be performing hits from his debut album "Dreams and Nightmares", and has already had collaborations with Mariah Carey and Drake, and over 21 million hits on YouTube!
